10:
Hm? Oh. Hi, Nimbus. Yeah, I'm fine.
I just found a weird note in my room.
Here, have a look.
14:
"It's treasure hunt time! Get out there
and find your trove! Love, Mia"
...What's that supposed to mean?
17:
I think she must of hid something of
mine, and now I'm supposed to go on
a "treasure hunt" to find it.
20:
Hide and seek? Oh c'mon.
How old is she?
25: Hey! Treasure hunts are for all ages!
30:
Especially ones hosted by Mia,
treasure hunter extraordinaire!
33:
Returned to the scene of the crime,
huh? C'mon Alk! Let's catch that thief
and get your stuff back!
38:
Thief?! I just said I was a treasure
hunter! Don't sell me short!
41: If you THIEVE, you're a thief.
44:
I didn't THIEVE anything! I just hid it!
I wanted to show Alk the thrill
of the hunt!
48:
Oh. Is that why you put a puzzle on
the back of the letter?
53:
Yeah! I hid a bunch of clues to lead
you to the treasure.
C'mon, it'll be a blast!
58:
Sounds more like a pain in the ass.
Alk, I can probably sniff it out.
I think it's—
63:
Hey! T-time out!
You can't do that! That's cheating!
69:
It's okay, Nimbus. Mia's treasure hunt
sounds fun, so I'll give it a go!
71:
Let's see... I'm guessing the first clue
is to head to the canal, right?
75: You're a natural, Alk! You've got this!
83:
I think I figured out where the treasure
is! The clues lead to... you, Mia!
93:
Huh? How'd you figure out Mia has
the treasure from this scribble of
a monster?
100: No way is that a tiger...
105:
Ahaha. I'll admit, I thought these
scratchy lines were cuts at first, but
they're probably supposed to be
tiger stripes.
110:
What do you mean, "supposed to be?"
They totally look like stripes! Anyways,
you won fair and square, so here's
your treasure!
115:
Big talk comin' from the one who
stole it in the first place.
So, what'd she nab?
125:
It's always handy to have in the
kitchen, so I guess you could call it
a "treasure." But wait...
132:
Oh, wow! This isn't just any old table
salt—it's top-grade stuff from
the Endless Blue!
140:
Yep! I saw it at the market and
thought Alk would like it! Best part
of the hunt is actually getting
the treasure, right?
146:
Th-thank you so much! I've actually
had my eye on this salt for a while.
I can't wait to try it!
149:
Am I missing something here?
Salt is salt.
152:
Maybe to you, but one man's trash is
another's treasure. If it makes
someone happy, it's treasure in my
books!
160:
Now that you've got the basics down,
we should try hunting for loot in some
old ruins sometime!
166:
A bona fide treasure hunt? Sure, that
sounds fun!
169:
Hey, Nimbus. You comin' with? For all
your mumbling and grumbling, you
seemed pretty into the puzzles.
175:
N-no, I wasn't! But I guess I could tag
along. Y'know, keep you two outta
trouble.
182:
Think of all the juicy treasures out
there just waiting for us! Let's not keep
them waiting, Alk!
